    "details": "In 1991, Diane Labenek and her family in Carp, Ontario began experiencing a series of extraordinary phenomena connected to observations of a red flame-like craft in their area. The encounters escalated to include nocturnal events, with Labenek's father reporting periods of paralysis. A scorched area was discovered in a field near the property. The family documented their experiences extensively on VHS tapes, which became known as 'The Guardian' tapes. Researcher Bob Oechsler of MUFON investigated the case. The combination of physical evidence, multiple witnesses, and video documentation makes the Carpenter/Labenek case one of the most unusual and thoroughly documented UFO-related cases in Canadian history.",
    "witness_account": "Diane Labenek was the primary witness. Family member (her father) reported being paralyzed at night, possibly related to the encounter. The family experienced ongoing phenomena that led to their involvement with MUFON and researcher Bob Oechsler. VHS tapes ('The Guardian' tapes) were made documenting the family's experiences.",
