    "details": "In 2021, a green light phenomenon over the Gulf of St. Lawrence was independently verified by personnel on both military and commercial aircraft. The event was officially filed under CADORS 2021Q2032 — the Canadian Aviation Difficulty/Occurrence Reporting System. CADORS is the official system by which aviation hazards, near-misses, and anomalous aerial phenomena are reported in Canada. The fact that this phenomenon was significant enough to be filed as an aviation occurrence, and that it was observed by two different aircraft types, makes it one of the strongest contemporary UFO cases in the Canadian record. It demonstrates that unidentified aerial phenomena continue to be observed in Canadian airspace and documented through official aviation channels.",
